  "texts": [
    "Data Feminism formulates core principles that emphasise necessary considerations: First, \"elevate emotion and embodiment\".",
    "This emphasises the importance of valuing input from individuals as \"living, feeling bodies in the world\" (D'ignazio and Klein 2020, p. 2, chapter 3)-beyond their expertise in computer science.",
    "Second, \"consider context\" advocates for examining a system's environment and to understand the values that motivate the system's creation (D'ignazio and Klein 2020).",
    "\"Embracing pluralism\" whilst doing so produces the most complete knowledge from synthesising all perspectives present and advocates for non-dominant forms of information (D'ignazio and Klein 2020).",
    "D'ignazio and Klein (2020) recommend investigating power structures in the given use case (principle 'examine power')."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}